{"closingIssuesReferences":[],"files":[{"path":"dream-server/scripts/bootstrap-upgrade.sh","additions":3,"deletions":3,"changeType":"MODIFIED"}],"reviewDecision":"CHANGES_REQUESTED","reviewRequests":[{"__typename":"User","login":"Lightheartdevs"}],"reviews":[{"id":"PRR_kwDORMI4oM72bz7u","author":{"login":"Lightheartdevs"},"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","body":"Correct — surrounding code uses `$DOCKER_CMD` but this line was genuinely missed. Worth noting that PR #975 touches the same file but only updates the preceding `docker ps` line, leaving this `docker restart` call unchanged — so this PR is not redundant with #975 and should merge either way. Ship.","submittedAt":"2026-04-18T14:01:09Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"reactionGroups":[],"state":"DISMISSED","commit":{"oid":"3e56eb70972d4e9002252830ffa7abeb408e846c"}},{"id":"PRR_kwDORMI4oM72cBVN","author":{"login":"Lightheartdevs"},"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","body":"**Dismissing my prior approval — deep audit found the fix is incomplete.**\n\nThe PR correctly changes `docker restart dream-dreamforge` at line 458 to use `$DOCKER_CMD`. But the same file has **two more bare `docker` calls immediately below**, in the very next code block (openclaw recreate):\n\n```bash\n# dream-server/scripts/bootstrap-upgrade.sh\n456:        if $DOCKER_CMD ps --filter name=dream-dreamforge ...  # ✓ correct\n457:            log \"Restarting DreamForge to pick up model change...\"\n458:            $DOCKER_CMD restart dream-dreamforge ...          # ✓ fixed by this PR\n459:        fi\n460:        # Recreate OpenClaw so inject-token.js picks up the new GGUF_FILE/LLM_MODEL\n461:        # from .env. A restart alone won't work — env vars are baked in at container\n462:        # creation time, and inject-token.js builds the Lemonade model name from them.\n463:        if docker ps --filter name=dream-openclaw ...          # ✗ STILL BARE\n464:            log \"Recreating OpenClaw to pick up model change...\"\n465:            if [[ ${#COMPOSE_ARGS[@]} -gt 0 ]]; then\n466:                docker compose \"${COMPOSE_ARGS[@]}\" up -d --force-recreate openclaw  # ✗ STILL BARE\n```\n\nThe rationale from your PR body — *\"on systems where the user isn't in the docker group and needs sudo docker\"* — applies identically to lines 463 and 466. The openclaw recreate block will fail on the same systems this PR is trying to support.\n\n**Suggested fix:** extend the PR to also change:\n- Line 463: `docker ps` → `$DOCKER_CMD ps`\n- Line 466: `docker compose \"${COMPOSE_ARGS[@]}\" up -d` → `$DOCKER_COMPOSE_CMD \"${COMPOSE_ARGS[@]}\" up -d`\n\n($DOCKER_COMPOSE_CMD is already set up in the detection block added earlier in this file — see the `if $DOCKER_CMD compose version` block.)\n\nHappy to re-approve with the complete fix. Apologies for the churn.","submittedAt":"2026-04-18T14:31:24Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"reactionGroups":[],"state":"CHANGES_REQUESTED","commit":{"oid":"3e56eb70972d4e9002252830ffa7abeb408e846c"}}],"statusCheckRollup":[{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-22T10:55:03Z","conclusion":"FAILURE","detailsUrl":"https://github.com/Light-Heart-Labs/DreamServer/actions/runs/24774440999/job/72488945124","name":"integration-smoke","startedAt":"2026-04-22T10:54:28Z","status":"COMPLETED","workflowName":"Test Linux"},{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-22T10:54:31Z","conclusion":"SUCCESS","detailsUrl":"https://github.com/Light-Heart-Labs/DreamServer/actions/runs/24774441086/job/72488945459","name":"Basic Review","startedAt":"2026-04-22T10:54:27Z","status":"COMPLETED","workflowName":"Claude Code Review"},{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-22T10:54:52Z","conclusion":"SUCCESS","detailsUrl":"https://github.com/Light-Heart-Labs/DreamServer/actions/runs/24774441056/job/72488945149","name":"frontend","startedAt":"2026-04-22T10:54:27Z","status":"COMPLETED","workflowName":"Dashboard"},{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-22T10:54:57Z","conclusion":"SUCCESS","detailsUrl":"https